 liable for personal injuries sustained by foster children only to the extent natural parents are liable to their children unless the injury was proximately caused by the willful and wanton misconduct of the foster parent toward the foster child or gross negligence in the standard of care provided by the foster parent for the foster child. Any recovery for personal injury arising out of participation in any farming or ranching activity in which natural children of an equivalent age commonly participate in the course of living, playing, or assisting their parents on a farm or ranch is specifically barred . 350 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.027 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 17421, "action_date": "2002-01-22T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 92570, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/92570.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 167, "committee_id_action": 769, "committee_id_assigned": 747, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 17421, "action_date": "2002-01-26T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 92671, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/92671.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 747, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 17421, "action_date": "2002-01-30T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 93213, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/93213.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 747, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 17421, "action_date": "2002-01-30T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 93213, "document_u